    "b-render-grid-mechanism-8": {
      "id": "b-render-grid-mechanism-8",
      "flavour": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "gridBackground",
          "attributes": {
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/stage/grid.ts",
              "symbol": "gridBackground"
            },
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " (in "
        },
        {
          "insert": "grid.ts",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ") computes the CSS "
        },
        {
          "insert": "backgroundSize",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "/"
        },
        {
          "insert": "backgroundPosition",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "/dot-radius for a zoom-aware dot grid pinned to world coordinates. The mechanism: starting from a world-space base step ("
        },
        {
          "insert": "GRID_BASE_STEP_PX",
          "attributes": {
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/stage/grid.ts",
              "symbol": "GRID_BASE_STEP_PX"
            },
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " = 8 logical px), the function computes the on-screen step as "
        },
        {
          "insert": "effectiveStep * scale",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ". If that on-screen size is below the minimum band, it repeatedly doubles "
        },
        {
          "insert": "effectiveStep",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " (a "
        },
        {
          "insert": "while",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " loop) until the on-screen step is back at or above the minimum; if it's above the maximum band, it repeatedly halves "
        },
        {
          "insert": "effectiveStep",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " until it falls back at or below the maximum. Because the step only ever changes by powers of two, the grid's on-screen density shifts in discrete tiers as zoom changes, while background size and pan position still move continuously within each tier — panning and continuous zoom inside one tier never causes a visible grid \"pop,\" only crossing a tier boundary does. Dot radius is handled separately: it scales continuously with zoom (not tiered) and is clamped between "
        },
        {
          "insert": "MIN_DOT_RADIUS_PX",
          "attributes": {
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/stage/grid.ts",
              "symbol": "MIN_DOT_RADIUS_PX"
            },
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " and "
        },
        {
          "insert": "MAX_DOT_RADIUS_PX",
          "attributes": {
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/stage/grid.ts",
              "symbol": "MAX_DOT_RADIUS_PX"
            },
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " so dots stay visible when zoomed far out and stop growing past a fixed size when zoomed far in — FigJam's dots read as a constant fine size on screen regardless of the current density tier."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-render-grid-band-9": {
      "id": "b-render-grid-band-9",
      "flavour": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The screen-space band the effective step must stay inside is "
        },
        {
          "insert": "[GRID_MIN_SCREEN_STEP_PX, GRID_MAX_SCREEN_STEP_PX]",
          "attributes": {
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "packages/canvas/src/stage/grid.ts",
              "symbol": "GRID_MIN_SCREEN_STEP_PX"
            },
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ", currently ~[6.5, 13] px ("
        },
        {
          "insert": "grid.ts",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " re-exports these as "
        },
        {
          "insert": "MIN_SCREEN_STEP_PX",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " / "
        },
        {
          "insert": "MAX_SCREEN_STEP_PX",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "). This band and the base step of 8 logical px were chosen to reproduce two pixel-sampled ground-truth observations from the FigJam reference captures: at zoom 0.305, the base step lands on tier n=2 (8 × 4 = 32 world px), giving 32 × 0.305 ≈ 9.8px on screen, matching the measured 9.8px; at zoom 0.21, the same tier gives 32 × 0.21 ≈ 6.7px, matching the measured 6.9px. Both observations resolve to the same underlying logical spacing (32px), which is what validated choosing 8 as the base step and powers-of-two as the step law rather than some other base."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-render-grid-decision-10": {
      "id": "b-render-grid-decision-10",
      "flavour": "decision",
      "props": {
        "status": "accepted",
        "title": "Keep the grid legible via a screen-pixel step band, not a fixed world step"
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "A fixed world-space grid step would either become imperceptibly dense (many sub-pixel dots merging into noise) when zoomed far out, or absurdly sparse (a single dot every few screen-feet) when zoomed far in. Instead, the grid's world-space step doubles or halves as needed to keep the on-screen step within a legible band (currently ~6.5–13px, "
        },
        {
          "insert": "GRID_MIN_SCREEN_STEP_PX",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "/"
        },
        {
          "insert": "GRID_MAX_SCREEN_STEP_PX",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " in "
        },
        {
          "insert": "grid.ts",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "), so the dot grid stays visually useful across the entire zoom range instead of only near 100%."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
